        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p>Protecting your personal information is our top priority.</p>
    </header>

    <div class="container">
        <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
        <p>This Privacy Policy explains how MentalQ (“we,” “our,” “us”) collects, uses, discloses, and protects your personal information when you use our mobile application (“App”). By using MentalQ, you agree to the terms outlined here.</p>

        <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
        <p>We collect the following types of information:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Personal Information:</strong> Information you provide during account creation, such as your name, email address, and age.</li>
            <li><strong>Journal Entries:</strong> Your written or audio-submitted journal entries, which are analyzed using AI for insights into your mental state.</li>
            <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> Information about how you interact with the App, including features used, session duration, and error logs.</li>
            <li><strong>Device Data:</strong> Information about the device you use to access the App, including operating system, device type, and unique identifiers.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <p>Your information is used for the following purposes:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>To provide personalized insights and recommendations based on your journal entries.</li>
            <li>To improve the functionality and performance of the App.</li>
            <li>To communicate with you about updates, support, or promotional content.</li>
            <li>To ensure compliance with legal obligations and maintain the security of our services.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>4. Data Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
        <p>We respect your privacy and do not sell your personal information. However, we may share your data in the following scenarios:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>With Service Providers:</strong> Trusted third-party providers who assist in App functionality (e.g., cloud hosting or AI analysis).</li>
            <li><strong>For Legal Reasons:</strong> If required by law, regulation, or court order.</li>
            <li><strong>In Case of Business Transfers:</strong> In connection with a merger, sale, or reorganization of our company.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>5. Data Security</h2>
        <p>We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your data against unauthorized access, loss, or misuse. Despite these measures, no system can guarantee absolute security.</p>

        <h2>6. Your Rights</h2>
        <p>You have the following rights regarding your data:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Access:</strong> Request a copy of the personal information we have about you.</li>
            <li><strong>Correction:</strong> Request updates to inaccurate or incomplete data.</li>
            <li><strong>Deletion:</strong> Request deletion of your data, subject to legal obligations.</li>
            <li><strong>Restriction:</strong> Request limits on how we use your data.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>To exercise these rights, contact us at <strong>privacy@mentalqapp.com</strong>.</p>

        <h2>7. Retention of Data</h2>
        <p>We retain your personal data only as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this policy or as required by law.</p>

        <h2>8. Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Significant changes will be communicated through the App or via email. Continued use of the App after updates constitutes acceptance of the revised policy.</p>

        <h2>9. Contact Us</h2>
